df-lgam
blocks.content: Define the log-Gamma function. We can work with this form of the gamma function a bit easier than the equivalent expression for the gamma function itself, and moreover this function is not actually equal to ` log ( _G ( x ) ) ` because the branch cuts are placed differently (we do have ` exp ( log_G ( x ) ) = _G ( x ) ` , though). This definition is attributed to Euler, and unlike the usual integral definition is defined on the entire complex plane except the nonpositive integers ` ZZ \ NN ` , where the function has simple poles. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 12-Jul-2014.)

blocks.name: df-gam
blocks.content: Define the Gamma function. See ~ df-lgam for more information about the reason for this definition in terms of the log-gamma function. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 12-Jul-2014.)

blocks.name: df-igam
blocks.content: Define the inverse Gamma function, which is defined everywhere, unlike the Gamma function itself. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 16-Jul-2017.)

blocks.name: eldmgm
blocks.content: Elementhood in the set of non-nonpositive integers. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 12-Jul-2014.)
blocks.origin:
thm eldmgm(class c0) {
  |- wb(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wa(wcel(c0, cc), wn(wcel(cneg(c0), cn0))))
} = {
  bitri(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wa(wcel(c0, cc), wn(wcel(cneg(c0), cn0))), wa(wcel(c0, cc), wn(wcel(c0, cdif(cz, cn)))))
  eldif(c0, cc, cdif(cz, cn))
  pm5.32i(wcel(c0, cc), wn(wcel(c0, cdif(cz, cn))), wn(wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)))
  notbid(wcel(c0, cc), wcel(c0, cdif(cz, cn)), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0))
  syl5bb(wcel(c0, cc), wcel(c0, cdif(cz, cn)), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0), wa(wcel(c0, cz), wn(wcel(c0, cn))))
  eldif(c0, cz, cn)
  impbid2(wcel(c0, cc), wa(wcel(c0, cz), wn(wcel(c0, cn))), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0))
  orcanai(wcel(c0, cz), wcel(c0, cn), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0))
  simprbi(wcel(c0, cz), wo(wcel(c0, cn), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)), wcel(c0, cr))
  elznn(c0)
  jca2(wcel(c0, cc), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0), wcel(c0, cz), wn(wcel(c0, cn)))
  ex(wcel(c0, cc), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0), wcel(c0, cz))
  eqeltrrd(c0, cz, cneg(cneg(c0)), wa(wcel(c0, cc), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)))
  adantr(wcel(c0, cc), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0), wceq(cneg(cneg(c0)), c0))
  negneg(c0)
  adantl(wcel(c0, cc), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0), wcel(cneg(cneg(c0)), cz))
  nn0negz(cneg(c0))
  nsyl3(wcel(cneg(c0), cn0), wcel(c0, cn), wbr(nat0, cle, cneg(c0)))
  mpbid(wcel(c0, cn), wn(wbr(nat0, cle, cneg(c0))), wbr(cneg(c0), clt, nat0))
  mpbid(wcel(c0, cn), wbr(cneg(c0), clt, nat0), wbr(nat0, clt, c0))
  nngt0(c0)
  lt0neg2d(c0, wcel(c0, cn))
  sylancl(wcel(c0, cn), wb(wbr(cneg(c0), clt, nat0), wn(wbr(nat0, cle, cneg(c0)))), wcel(cneg(c0), cr), wcel(nat0, cr))
  renegcld(c0, wcel(c0, cn))
  nnre(c0)
  0re()
  ltnle(cneg(c0), nat0)
  nn0ge0(cneg(c0))
}
blocks.pretty:
thm eldmgm(class c0) {
  ⊢ (c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ))↔(c0 ∈ ℂ ∧ ¬ -u(c0)∈ ℕ0))
} = {
  bitri(c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ)), (c0 ∈ ℂ ∧ ¬ -u(c0)∈ ℕ0), (c0 ∈ ℂ ∧ ¬ c0 ∈(ℤ \ ℕ)))
  eldif(c0, cc, (ℤ \ ℕ))
  pm5.32i(c0 ∈ ℂ, ¬ c0 ∈(ℤ \ ℕ), ¬ -u(c0)∈ ℕ0)
  notbid(c0 ∈ ℂ, c0 ∈(ℤ \ ℕ), -u(c0)∈ ℕ0)
  syl5bb(c0 ∈ ℂ, c0 ∈(ℤ \ ℕ), -u(c0)∈ ℕ0, (c0 ∈ ℤ ∧ ¬ c0 ∈ ℕ))
  eldif(c0, cz, cn)
  impbid2(c0 ∈ ℂ, (c0 ∈ ℤ ∧ ¬ c0 ∈ ℕ), -u(c0)∈ ℕ0)
  orcanai(c0 ∈ ℤ, c0 ∈ ℕ, -u(c0)∈ ℕ0)
  simprbi(c0 ∈ ℤ, (c0 ∈ ℕ ∨ -u(c0)∈ ℕ0), c0 ∈ ℝ)
  elznn(c0)
  jca2(c0 ∈ ℂ, -u(c0)∈ ℕ0, c0 ∈ ℤ, ¬ c0 ∈ ℕ)
  ex(c0 ∈ ℂ, -u(c0)∈ ℕ0, c0 ∈ ℤ)
  eqeltrrd(c0, cz, -u(-u(c0)), (c0 ∈ ℂ ∧ -u(c0)∈ ℕ0))
  adantr(c0 ∈ ℂ, -u(c0)∈ ℕ0, -u(-u(c0))= c0)
  negneg(c0)
  adantl(c0 ∈ ℂ, -u(c0)∈ ℕ0, -u(-u(c0))∈ ℤ)
  nn0negz(-u(c0))
  nsyl3(-u(c0)∈ ℕ0, c0 ∈ ℕ, 0[≤]-u(c0))
  mpbid(c0 ∈ ℕ, ¬ 0[≤]-u(c0), -u(c0)[<]0)
  mpbid(c0 ∈ ℕ, -u(c0)[<]0, 0[<]c0)
  nngt0(c0)
  lt0neg2d(c0, c0 ∈ ℕ)
  sylancl(c0 ∈ ℕ, (-u(c0)[<]0 ↔ ¬ 0[≤]-u(c0)), -u(c0)∈ ℝ, 0 ∈ ℝ)
  renegcld(c0, c0 ∈ ℕ)
  nnre(c0)
  0re()
  ltnle(-u(c0), nat0)
  nn0ge0(-u(c0))
}

blocks.name: dmgmaddn0
blocks.content: If ` A ` is not a nonpositive integer, then ` A + N ` is nonzero for any nonnegative integer ` N ` . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 12-Jul-2014.)
blocks.origin:
thm dmgmaddn0(class c0, class c1) {
  |- wi(wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wcel(c1, cn0)), wne(co(c0, caddc, c1), nat0))
} = {
  mpd(wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wcel(c1, cn0)), wne(co(c0, caddc, c1), nat0), wn(wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)))
  adantr(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wcel(c1, cn0), wn(wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)))
  simprbi(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wn(wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)), wcel(c0, cc))
  eldmgm(c0)
  necon3bd(co(c0, caddc, c1), nat0, wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wcel(c1, cn0)), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0))
  sylbird(wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wcel(c1, cn0)), wceq(co(c0, caddc, c1), nat0), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0), wceq(cneg(c0), c1))
  syl5bb(wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wcel(c1, cn0)), wceq(cneg(c0), c1), wceq(co(c0, caddc, c1), nat0), wceq(co(nat0, cmin, c0), c1))
  eqeq1i(cneg(c0), c1, co(nat0, cmin, c0))
  df-neg(c0)
  subaddd(nat0, c0, c1, wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wcel(c1, cn0)))
  0cnd(wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wcel(c1, cn0)))
  adantr(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wcel(c1, cn0), wcel(c0, cc))
  eldifi(c0, cc, cdif(cz, cn))
  adantl(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wcel(c1, cn0), wcel(c1, cc))
  nn0cn(c1)
  syl5ibrcom(wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wcel(c1, cn0)), wceq(cneg(c0), c1), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0), wcel(c1, cn0))
  simpr(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wcel(c1, cn0))
  eleq1(cneg(c0), c1, cn0)
}
blocks.pretty:
thm dmgmaddn0(class c0, class c1) {
  ⊢ ((c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ))∧ c1 ∈ ℕ0)→(c0[+]c1)≠ 0)
} = {
  mpd((c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ))∧ c1 ∈ ℕ0), (c0[+]c1)≠ 0, ¬ -u(c0)∈ ℕ0)
  adantr(c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ)), c1 ∈ ℕ0, ¬ -u(c0)∈ ℕ0)
  simprbi(c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ)), ¬ -u(c0)∈ ℕ0, c0 ∈ ℂ)
  eldmgm(c0)
  necon3bd((c0[+]c1), nat0, (c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ))∧ c1 ∈ ℕ0), -u(c0)∈ ℕ0)
  sylbird((c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ))∧ c1 ∈ ℕ0), (c0[+]c1)= 0, -u(c0)∈ ℕ0, -u(c0)= c1)
  syl5bb((c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ))∧ c1 ∈ ℕ0), -u(c0)= c1, (c0[+]c1)= 0, (0[-]c0)= c1)
  eqeq1i(-u(c0), c1, (0[-]c0))
  df-neg(c0)
  subaddd(nat0, c0, c1, (c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ))∧ c1 ∈ ℕ0))
  0cnd((c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ))∧ c1 ∈ ℕ0))
  adantr(c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ)), c1 ∈ ℕ0, c0 ∈ ℂ)
  eldifi(c0, cc, (ℤ \ ℕ))
  adantl(c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ)), c1 ∈ ℕ0, c1 ∈ ℂ)
  nn0cn(c1)
  syl5ibrcom((c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ))∧ c1 ∈ ℕ0), -u(c0)= c1, -u(c0)∈ ℕ0, c1 ∈ ℕ0)
  simpr(c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ)), c1 ∈ ℕ0)
  eleq1(-u(c0), c1, cn0)
}

blocks.name: dmlogdmgm
blocks.content: If ` A ` is in the continuous domain of the logarithm, then it is in the domain of the Gamma function. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 8-Jul-2017.)
blocks.origin:
thm dmlogdmgm(class c0) {
  |- wi(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))))
} = {
  sylanbrc(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wcel(c0, cc), wn(wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)))
  pm2.65da(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0), wbr(nat0, cle, cneg(c0)))
  nn0ge0d(cneg(c0), wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)))
  mpbid(wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)), wn(wbr(nat0, cle, cneg(c0))), wbr(cneg(c0), clt, nat0))
  mpbid(wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)), wbr(cneg(c0), clt, nat0), wbr(nat0, clt, c0))
  rpgt0d(c0, wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)))
  syldan(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0), wcel(c0, crp), wcel(c0, cr))
  imp(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wcel(c0, cr), wcel(c0, crp))
  simprbi(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wi(wcel(c0, cr), wcel(c0, crp)), wcel(c0, cc))
  ellogdm(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0)))
  eqid(cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0)))
  lt0neg2d(c0, wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)))
  negrebd(c0, wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)))
  adantr(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0), wcel(c0, cc))
  eldifi(c0, cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))
  ltnled(cneg(c0), nat0, wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)))
  nn0red(cneg(c0), wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)))
  simpr(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0))
  0red(wa(wcel(c0, cdif(cc, co(cmnf, cioc, nat0))), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)))
  eldmgm(c0)
}

blocks.name: dmgmaddnn0
blocks.content: If ` A ` is not a nonpositive integer and ` N ` is a nonnegative integer, then ` A + N ` is also not a nonpositive integer. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 6-Jul-2017.)
blocks.origin:
thm dmgmaddnn0(class c0, class c1, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wcel(co(c0, caddc, c1), cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c1, cn0))
} = {
  sylanbrc(w0, wcel(co(c0, caddc, c1), cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wcel(co(c0, caddc, c1), cc), wn(wcel(cneg(co(c0, caddc, c1)), cn0)))
  addcld(c0, c1, w0)
  mtand(w0, wcel(cneg(co(c0, caddc, c1)), cn0), wcel(cneg(c0), cn0))
  simprd(w0, wn(wcel(cneg(c0), cn0)), wcel(c0, cc))
  sylib(w0, wa(wcel(c0, cc), wn(wcel(cneg(c0), cn0))), wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))))
  eldmgm(c0)
  eqeltrrd(cneg(c0), cn0, co(cneg(co(c0, caddc, c1)), caddc, c1), wa(w0, wcel(cneg(co(c0, caddc, c1)), cn0)))
  adantr(w0, wcel(cneg(co(c0, caddc, c1)), cn0), wceq(co(cneg(co(c0, caddc, c1)), caddc, c1), cneg(c0)))
  eqtrd(co(cneg(co(c0, caddc, c1)), caddc, c1), cneg(c0), co(co(cneg(c0), cmin, c1), caddc, c1), w0)
  oveq1d(cneg(co(c0, caddc, c1)), caddc, c1, co(cneg(c0), cmin, c1), w0)
  negdi2d(c0, c1, w0)
  npcand(cneg(c0), c1, w0)
  negcld(c0, w0)
  eldifad(c0, cc, cdif(cz, cn), w0)
  nn0cnd(c1, w0)
  nn0addcld(cneg(co(c0, caddc, c1)), c1, wa(w0, wcel(cneg(co(c0, caddc, c1)), cn0)))
  simpr(w0, wcel(cneg(co(c0, caddc, c1)), cn0))
  adantr(w0, wcel(cneg(co(c0, caddc, c1)), cn0), wcel(c1, cn0))
  eldmgm(co(c0, caddc, c1))
}

blocks.name: dmgmdivn0
blocks.content: Lemma for ~ lgamf . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 3-Jul-2017.)
blocks.origin:
thm dmgmdivn0(class c0, class c1, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wne(co(co(c0, cdiv, c1), caddc, nat1), nat0))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c1, cn))
} = {
  eqnetrrd(co(co(c0, cdiv, c1), caddc, nat1), nat0, co(co(c0, caddc, c1), cdiv, c1), w0)
  eqtrd(co(co(c0, caddc, c1), cdiv, c1), co(co(c0, cdiv, c1), caddc, nat1), co(co(c0, cdiv, c1), caddc, co(c1, cdiv, c1)), w0)
  divdird(c0, c1, c1, w0)
  oveq2d(co(c0, cdiv, c1), caddc, co(c1, cdiv, c1), nat1, w0)
  dividd(c1, w0)
  divne0d(co(c0, caddc, c1), c1, w0)
  addcld(c0, c1, w0)
  eldifad(c0, cc, cdif(cz, cn), w0)
  nncnd(c1, w0)
  syl2anc(w0, wne(co(c0, caddc, c1), nat0), wcel(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))), wcel(c1, cn0))
  nnnn0d(c1, w0)
  dmgmaddn0(c0, c1)
  nnne0d(c1, w0)
}
blocks.pretty:
thm dmgmdivn0(class c0, class c1, wff w0) {
  ⊢ (w0 →((c0[÷]c1)[+]1)≠ 0)
  ⊣ (w0 → c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ)))
  ⊣ (w0 → c1 ∈ ℕ)
} = {
  eqnetrrd(((c0[÷]c1)[+]1), nat0, ((c0[+]c1)[÷]c1), w0)
  eqtrd(((c0[+]c1)[÷]c1), ((c0[÷]c1)[+]1), ((c0[÷]c1)[+](c1[÷]c1)), w0)
  divdird(c0, c1, c1, w0)
  oveq2d((c0[÷]c1), caddc, (c1[÷]c1), nat1, w0)
  dividd(c1, w0)
  divne0d((c0[+]c1), c1, w0)
  addcld(c0, c1, w0)
  eldifad(c0, cc, (ℤ \ ℕ), w0)
  nncnd(c1, w0)
  syl2anc(w0, (c0[+]c1)≠ 0, c0 ∈(ℂ \(ℤ \ ℕ)), c1 ∈ ℕ0)
  nnnn0d(c1, w0)
  dmgmaddn0(c0, c1)
  nnne0d(c1, w0)
}

blocks.name: lgamgulmlem1
blocks.content: Lemma for ~ lgamgulm . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 3-Jul-2017.)
blocks.origin:
thm lgamgulmlem1(setvar s0, setvar s1, class c0, class c1, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wss(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn))))
  -| wi(w0, wcel(c1, cn))
  -| wceq(c0, crab(s0, cc, wa(wbr(cfv(cabs, cv(s0)), cle, c1), wral(s1, cn0, wbr(co(nat1, cdiv, c1), cle, cfv(cabs, co(cv(s0), caddc, cv(s1))))))))
  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffsc(s0, c1)
  -| diffsc(s1, c1)
  -| diffsw(s0, w0)
} = {
  a1ii(wi(w0, wss(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn)))), diffsc(s0, c1))
  syl5eqss(c0, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn)), crab(s0, cc, wa(wbr(cfv(cabs, cv(s0)), cle, c1), wral(s1, cn0, wbr(co(nat1, cdiv, c1), cle, cfv(cabs, co(cv(s0), caddc, cv(s1))))))), w0)
  rabssdv(s0, cc, cdif(cc, cdif(cz, cn)), w0, wa(wbr(cfv(cabs, cv(s0)), cle, c1), wral(s1, cn0, wbr(co(nat1, cdiv, c1), cle, cfv(cabs, co(cv(s0), caddc, cv(s1)))))))

blocks.name: lgamgulmlem6
blocks.content: The series ` G ` is uniformly convergent on the compact region ` U ` , which describes a circle of radius ` R ` with holes of size ` 1 / R ` around the poles of the gamma function. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 9-Jul-2017.)

blocks.content: The ` U ` regions used in the proof of ~ lgamgulm have interiors which cover the entire domain of the Gamma function. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 6-Jul-2017.)

thm lgamucov2(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, class c0, class c1, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wrex(s0, cn, wcel(c0, c1)))

  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffss(s0, s2)
  -| diffss(s1, s2)

  -| diffsc(s1, c0)
  -| diffsc(s2, c0)
  -| diffsw(s0, w0)
  -| diffsw(s1, w0)
  -| diffsw(s2, w0)
} = {
  syl(w0, wrex(s0, cn, wcel(c0, c1)), wrex(s0, cn, wcel(c0, cfv(cfv(cnt, cfv(ctopn, ccnfld)), c1))))
  lgamucov(s0, s1, s2, c0, cfv(ctopn, ccnfld), c1, w0)
  reximi(s0, cn, wcel(c0, cfv(cfv(cnt, cfv(ctopn, ccnfld)), c1)), wcel(c0, c1))
  sseli(c0, cfv(cfv(cnt, cfv(ctopn, ccnfld)), c1), c1)
  mp2an(wss(cfv(cfv(cnt, cfv(ctopn, ccnfld)), c1), c1), wcel(cfv(ctopn, ccnfld), ctop), wss(c1, cc))
  cnfldtop(cfv(ctopn, ccnfld))
  eqid(cfv(ctopn, ccnfld))
  ssrab3(s1, c1, cc, wa(wbr(cfv(cabs, cv(s1)), cle, cv(s0)), wral(s2, cn0, wbr(co(nat1, cdiv, cv(s0)), cle, cfv(cabs, co(cv(s1), caddc, cv(s2)))))))
